"{\"uid\": \"eonline.com-news-1405716-2024-olympics-what-made-triathlete-tyler-mislawchuk-throw-up-10-times-after-swim-in-seine-river\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Tyler Mislawchuk, a Canadian triathlete, explained why he vomited several times after his race during the 2024 Olympics in Paris, where he swam in the Seine River.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tyler Mislawchuk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Mislawchuk\"}, {\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9663456022313478, \"rank\": 0.03482635753072107, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.546482268489071e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tyler Mislawchukknows that to be successful, one has to give it their all.\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And sometimes, that comes with a whole lot of puke.\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the athlete, who represented Canada in the2024 Paris Olympics, went viralfor throwing up 10 timesafterswimmingin the Seine Riverduring the men's triathlon July 31, he gave insight into whatreallycaused his upset stomach.\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 328, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9570496690963007, \"rank\": 0.0447870098843947, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I happened to swallow a lot of water during the race,\\\" Tyler toldCBCAug.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Nothing to do with the quality.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My stomach was just extremely full, and so that ended up being a limiting factor for me in the race.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You put that with one hour, 40 minutes of going as hard as you can, stuff's going to happen.\\\"\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old, who placed 9th in the competition, did not expect his post-race moment to make headlines.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laughing, he added, \\\"It's all over the internet and it's not why I want to go viral.\\\"\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The weather was also a factor.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Being from Canada, where he emphasized how cold it can get, he's not quite acclimated to France's summer weather, either.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9570496690963007, \"rank\": 0.0447870098843947, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9988017535370407, \"rank\": 0.0011984926716004114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that did not stop Tyler-who had to withdraw from the 2020 Tokyo Games due to an Achilles injury-from giving it his all.\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1258, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 1.2479260295595578e-11, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At my last Olympics there was the injury and with all the stuff that happened there was a lot of 'what ifs,'\\\" he explained toTriathlon Magazinein an interview published July 31.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have no 'what ifs' on the day, I went for it, it was absolutely everything.\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I vomited 10 times after the race \\u2026 it got hot in the last laps.\\\"\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not surprising that theSeine River's water quality came into questionwhen he started vomiting, as theirrace was postponedfrom its initial July 30 start date due to unsafe levels of fecal matter following heavy rain.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tyler wasn't the only athlete to speak about the Seine's water quality.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1846, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Brennan\", \"score\": 0.9999997338145831, \"rank\": 2.611427682089412e-07, \"text\": \"Tyler\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Brennan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tyler_Brennan\"}, {\"begin\": 1895, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.2412384089568504e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgian triathleteJolien Vermeylen, who competed in the women's race after the men's, shared her less than impressed decision to hold the competitions in the famed river.\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1918, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9989012399907798, \"rank\": 0.0010979381764197314, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While swimming under the bridge, I felt and saw things that we should not think about too much,\\\" shetold reporters.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Seine has been dirty for a hundred years, so they can not say that the safety of the athletes is a priority.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2212, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.2412384089568504e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's bulls--t!\\\"\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the 2024 Olympics, the city of Parisspent $1.5 billion to clean upthe Seine, where swimming had been banned since 1923.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2419, \"end\": 2424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.2412384089568504e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To soothe critics' concerns, the city's mayorAnne Hidalgo, Paris 2024 Olympic PresidentTony Estanguetand other officials took a swim in the river to prove its safety.\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2519, \"end\": 2526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999997853238032, \"rank\": 2.1467629686712205e-07, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}, {\"begin\": 2528, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.259262338106458e-27, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The water is wonderful,\\\" Anne toldNBC Newsafter her swim July 17, noting that the water was \\\"very cool and very nice.\\\"\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Keep reading for more moments at the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(E!\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News and NBC News are part of the NBCUniversal family.)\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2824, \"end\": 2832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9901774582326542, \"rank\": 0.00885769304